clinicalDescription: Overview: Delivery, after the 20th week of pregnancy, of a baby who has died. Loss of a baby before the 20th week of pregnancy is a miscarriagePresentation: Baby born without signs of life, fetal death Assessment: Mother reports change in fetal activity, No fetal movement is present (ultrasound). Pregnancy or birth complications, mother risk factors Plan: Induction of labor, dilation and evacuation. Autopsy on the baby and other laboratory tests to understand why the baby died before birthPrognosis: A baby is stillborn in about 1 in 200 pregnancies, oftern cause is not known.
